int in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Inés González Girón was born in 1218, in Spain, her father, Gonzalo Ruiz de Ceballos, was 58 and her mother, Marquesa Dama Pérez de Villalobos, was 33. She had at least 1 son with Diego Gutierrez de Caviedes."},"et":{"1218–":"1218–Surnud","1218–Female":"1218–Surnud","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1221–Male":"1221–Surnud","1223–Female":"1223–Surnud","–1266":"–1266","–1353":"–1353","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1160–1236":"1160–1236","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1236":"1236","1223":"1223","1200":"1200","1266":"1266","1255":"1255","1353":"1353","1221":"1221","1218":"1218","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Caviedes, Valdáliga, Cantabria, España":"Caviedes, Valdáliga, Cantabria, Hispaania","Spain":"Hispaania"},"fi":{"1218–":"1218–Kuollut","1218–Female":"1218–Kuollut","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1221–Male":"1221–Kuollut","1223–Female":"1223–Kuollut","–1266":"–1266","–1353":"–1353","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1160–1236":"1160–1236","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1236":"1236","1223":"1223","1200":"1200","1266":"1266","1255":"1255","1353":"1353","1221":"1221","1218":"1218","about 1230":"noin 1230","Caviedes, Valdáliga, Cantabria, España":"Caviedes, Valdáliga, Cantabria, Espanja","Spain":"Espanja"},"fr":{"1218–":"1218–Décédée","1218–Female":"1218–Décédée","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1221–Male":"1221–Décéd